data.title: American Youth Football
data.text:
Academic All- American Award Recipients

Scholastic and Academic Awards

Scholastic scholarships and Academic Alliance awards are given to those AYF/AYC athletes who shine the brightest. Each year over 20 athletes are recognized in several award categories with significant monetary funds based on their achievements and exemplary behavior in leadership. These funds help to offset academic expenses.

Academic Achievement Alliance Awards

Participating in sports enables athletes to excel on and off the turf and grow in all areas of their lives. Academic Alliance acknowledges scholar athletes who have proven themselves to be a paradigm of the FOUR PILLARS of achievement including Academics, Respect, Discipline and Performance.

Academic All-Americans

Scholastic awards are given to those AYF/AYC athletes who shine the brightest in the classroom and in extra-curricular activities. Our Academic All-American program recognizes student athletes who achieve the Platinum Level (Over 100% GPA), Gold Level (96% to 100% GPA), Silver (90% to 95.9% GPA) and Bronze (80% to 89.9% GPA).

Academic Achievement Alliance Scholarships

Each year, two athletes from each region are selected to receive our Academic All-American Scholarship for post-secondary education, named in honor of an AYF Hall of Fame Member. Additionally, one of these athletes is chosen as our Academic Achievement Alliance âTop Scholarâ and receives an additional scholarship for post-secondary education, named in honor of Mr. Carl Allegretti, an AYF Hall of Fame Inductee and generous supporter.
